!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

realistic /ˌrɪəˈlɪstɪk/

1. ADJ If you are realistic about a situation, you recognize and accept its true nature and try to deal with it in a practical way. 现实的; 务实的 

例： Police have to be realistic about violent crime. 警察对暴力犯罪不得不采取务实的态度。 

2. realistically ADV 现实地; 务实地 

例： As an adult, you can assess the situation realistically. 作为成年人，你可以现实地估量这个局势。 

3. ADJ Something such as a goal or target that is realistic is one that you can sensibly expect to achieve. 现实可行的 

例： A more realistic figure is 11 million. 一个更现实可行的数字是1100万。 

4. ADJ You say that a painting, story, or movie is realistic when the people and things in it are like people and things in real life. 逼真的 

例： ...extraordinarily realistic paintings of Indians. …关于印第安人的极其逼真的绘画。 

5. realistically ADV 逼真地 

例： The film starts off realistically and then develops into a ridiculous fantasy. 电影开始的时候比较逼真，然后却发展成为荒谬的幻想。

</div>

